Ubuntu Tweak 0.4.6
=================
2009-03-02

New features:
- Full features support for Ubuntu 9.04.
- Added more third-party sources: Gnome global menu, gwibber, Chromium brower, Ubuntu Tweak testing, AWN testing, Specto.

Bugs fixed:
- Fixed #298300, cannot run 0.4.2 without compiz installed
- Fixed #331050, Error with 3rd party repositories
- Fixed #332110, it crashed before beginning
- Fixed #329310, load "Personal->Templates" error. version 0.4.5
- Fixed #330113, Wrong info about GScrot in "Applications -> Third-party sources"
- Fixed #331120, Ubuntu Tweak 0.4.5 give a error message when i go to Startup
- Fixed #332240, Improve usability in shortcut.py
- Fixed #332277, Patch for the error dialog
- Fixed #329607, A message typo
- Fixed the bug which can't clean the config files.


Ubuntu Tweak 0.4.5
=================

New features:

* Cleaner now can clean the package configs.
* Added a preferences dialog for Ubuntu Tweak.
* Default launch feature for Ubuntu Tweak.
* Friendly debug information.

Bug fixes:
* DropBox repository is out-of-date. (LP: #308395)
* Update Manager doesn't work. (LP: #308400)
* Repository is not signed. (LP: #312175)
* Add/Remove incorrect dialog (LP: #316191)
* Incorrect templates of ODS files. (LP: #308479)
* Typo. (LP: #310165, LP: #322057)
* Templates can't open. (LP: #319380)

Other changes:
* Rewrite the convert scripts.
* Process the status of app install/remove
* Rewrite the factory, now more powerful and flexible.
* Make the GNOME Panel icon setting revertable
* Signed every PPA repos.
